Police in Kisumu have arrested a suspect for obtaining money by false pretence. The suspect, Susan Kerubo Muhindi, was arrested by officers from Kondele Police Station at Polyview estate in Kisumu Central sub-county. Kerubo allegedly obtained Sh 400,000 by false pretence. The case had been reported at Nakuru Police station. Kisumu county criminal investigation officer (CCIO) Francis Wanjau confirmed the arrest. "It is true the suspect was arrested for obtaining money by false pretence. She will be collected by officers from Nakuru," he said. The case is being investigated by Nakuru county criminal investigation officers. Wanjau said Kerubo is in custody at Kondele Police Station awaiting collection by DCI officers from Nakuru county. Nakuru CCIO Anthony Sunguti confirmed that the matter was reported at the Nakuru police station. “We are investigating the case and officers from Nakuru have gone to Kisumu to collect the suspect,” Sunguti told the Star on phone.